node.text: Welcome to Jesse's Cookie Club, our brand-new series, where @jesseszewczyk calls up some of his favorite bakers and bakes up one of their signature cookie recipes together. node.text: @kiacooks credits her mom and grandma for instilling in her a love of good food and cooking, and in today’s episode of Secret Family Recipe, Kia makes one of her grandma’s signature dishes, Chicken & Stuff, with an assist from her mom. Along the way, Kia tweaks things here and there (blanched green beans instead of canned; sautéed chicken instead of boiled) to make the recipe her own while she and her mom talk about the origins of this delicious dish with the whimsical name. Tap the link in our bio for Kia’s family recipe. #thekitchn

node.title: Secret Family Recipe: Chicken & Stuff with @kiacooks

“For so many, especially in BIPOC communities, food is emblematic of their culture. In seeing how the Bangladeshi cuisine that I hold so close is so often overlooked, even neglected, in food media, I can’t help but think of all the cuisines and their people who are left out of the conversation,” writes @sweettemptationsbykayla. “Their recipes and stories need to be celebrated beyond their own communities. It’s not enough anymore to say that all are welcome at the table: There needs to actually be a seat for everyone.”

Tap our link in bio to read more about Kayla's five-part At the Table series, which starts this month with a conversation with her mom and her recipe for one of their family’s favorite foods: aloo chop. (Images: @ghazallephoto) #thekitchn
